Bank of Japan  Governor Haruhiko
Kuroda speaks today in parliament in Tokyo.
* Yields could rise if BOJ seen financing government debt:
Kuroda
* Govt decision to raise sales-tax rate makes govt-BOJ
commitment on fiscal reconstruction clearer; was a very
significant decision
* Expect CPI to gradually shift upwards: Kuroda
* BOJ still aims to achieve 2% inflation target within two
years: Kuroda
* NOTE: BOJ today raised its assessment of economic conditions
in all nine regions of Japan in its quarterly Sakura report;
cites improvement in employment, income and production
* NOTE: BOJ on Oct. 4 refrained from adding to unprecedented
